data.title: The Complete Pacific Jazz Recordings Of The Gerry Mulligan Quartet With Chet Baker - Gerry Mulligan
data.meta_description: The Complete Pacific Jazz Recordings Of The Gerry Mulligan Quartet With Chet Baker from Gerry Mulligan (1996) (CD). And other albums from Gerry Mulligan are available on sale at Recordsale.Gerry Mulligan, born in 1927, was an influential American jazz saxophonist, composer, and arranger. Emerging as a prominent figure in the West Coast jazz scene of the 1950s, Mulligan's distinctive baritone saxophone sound became iconic. He gained fame as a key member of the "cool jazz" movement, collaborating with musicians like Chet Baker. Mulligan's compositions, including "Walkin' Shoes" and "Line for Lyons," are celebrated jazz standards. His career encompassed various styles, from bebop to big band arrangements. Mulligan's innovative approach to jazz arranging left an indelible mark on the genre. He passed away in 1996, leaving a lasting legacy in jazz.
